<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="519" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[132,775,216,401]" box="[132,222,216,242]" pageId="14" pageNumber="519">REMARK</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[132,775,216,401]" pageId="14" pageNumber="519">
This species is known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[523,619,247,273]" pageId="14" pageNumber="519">holotype</typeStatus>
and two 
<typeStatus pageId="14" pageNumber="519">paratypes</typeStatus>
. According to morphological evalutions, it shows affinity to 
<taxonomicName authority="Blanford, 1874" authorityName="Blanford" authorityYear="1874" box="[227,571,311,337]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Eremias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="14" pageNumber="519" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fasciata">
<emphasis box="[227,395,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="519">Eremias fasciata</emphasis>
Blanford, 1874
</taxonomicName>
, but its subgeneric position remains unclear (
<bibRefCitation author="DAREVSKY I. S. &amp; SHCHERBAK N. N." box="[434,767,343,369]" pageId="14" pageNumber="519" pagination="13 - 15" refId="ref19636" refString="DAREVSKY I. S. &amp; SHCHERBAK N. N. 1978. - Eremias andersoni, a New Lizard (Reptilia, Lacertilia, Lacertidae) from Iran. Journal of Herpetology 12 (1): 13 - 15. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 1563496" type="journal article" year="1978">Darevsky &amp; Shcherbak 1978</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="ANDERSON S. C." box="[132,302,375,401]" pageId="14" pageNumber="519" refId="ref17788" refString="ANDERSON S. C. 1999. - The Lizards of Iran. Society for the study of amphibians and reptiles, Ithaca, New York, USA. 442 p." type="book" year="1999">Anderson 1999</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
